# tanchao.xyz — Cursor Rules

This is a static Astro 6 blog. See AGENTS.md for the full project guide.

## Key conventions

- **Framework**: Astro 6, Tailwind CSS v4, TypeScript strict mode
- **Content**: Posts in `src/content/posts/YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md`, Notes in `src/content/notes/slug.md`, Projects in `src/content/projects/slug.md`
- **URLs**: Posts → `/posts/YYYY/MM/DD/slug/`, Notes → `/notes/slug/`, Projects → `/projects/slug/`
- **Helpers**: `postSlug/postUrl`, `noteSlug/noteUrl`, `projectSlug/projectUrl`, `sortedProjects` all live in `src/lib/posts.ts`
- **Styling**: Use CSS variables (`var(--text)`, `var(--link)`, etc.) defined in `src/styles/global.css` — do NOT hardcode colors
- **Dark mode**: Controlled by `.dark` class on `<html>` — use CSS variables, not Tailwind `dark:` prefix
- **No Decap CMS**: Content is authored in the editor and pushed via git

## Voice and thinking

- Before any writing or content work — including turning a skeleton/outline into a draft — read `docs/voice.md`, the single source of truth for TC's voice and thinking.
- When TC hands you a skeleton, expand it, then surface and confirm missing or applicable gaps with TC before filling them in. Don't silently omit or invent.

## When editing content files

- Validate frontmatter against the schema in `src/content.config.ts`
- Never invent or hallucinate dates
- `title` max 80 characters
- Slugs must be kebab-case
- Run `npm run check:content` after editing frontmatter

## When editing Astro components

- Keep styles inline using `style=""` with CSS variables, or use Tailwind utility classes
- Components receive typed Props interfaces — always define them
- Use `font-family:var(--font-sans)` for UI text, `font-family:var(--font-serif)` for body

## Commands

```
npm run dev
npm run build
npm run check
npm run check:content
npm run new:post -- "Title"
npm run new:project -- "Title"
npm run sync:substack
```
